classDiagram
    class Window {
        <<type alias>>
        datetime start
        datetime end
    }

    class Task {
        +str activity_description
        +date due_date
        +time start_time
        +str frequency
        +int duration_minutes
        +int priority
        +bool completed
        +bool flexible
        +time? earliest_start
        +time? latest_end
        +int buffer_minutes
        +date? series_start
        +datetime start_datetime
        +date anchor_date
        +Recurrence recurrence
        +mark_complete() None
        +get_end_time() datetime
        +calculate_next_start() datetime
        +calculate_next_due_date() date
        +with_due_date(due_date date) Task
        +with_start_time(start_time time) Task
        +with_datetime(moment datetime, series_start date?) Task
    }

    class Recurrence {
        +str kind
        +int interval
        +tuple~int~ weekdays
        +bool is_recurring
        +next_after(moment datetime, anchor date?) datetime
        +occurrences_in(base datetime, start datetime, end datetime) List~datetime~
    }

    class Pet {
        +str name
        +str species
        +date birth_date
        +List~Task~ tasks
        +add_task(task Task) None
        +add_tasks(tasks List~Task~) None
        +get_tasks() List~Task~
        +owns(task Task) bool
    }

    class Owner {
        +str name
        +List~Pet~ pets
        +List~Window~ available_windows
        +List~Window~ unavailable_windows
        +add_pet(pet Pet) None
        +get_pets() List~Pet~
        +get_all_tasks() List~Task~
        +find_pet_for_task(task Task) Pet?
        +get_available_windows() List~Window~
        +get_unavailable_windows() List~Window~
        +is_available(time datetime, end_time datetime) bool
        +add_available_window(window Window) None
        +add_unavailable_window(window Window) None
    }

    class Scheduler {
        +Owner owner
        +get_all_tasks() List~Task~
        +sort_by_time() List~Task~
        +filter_tasks(pet Pet, pet_name str, completed bool, available_only bool) List~Task~
        +detect_conflicts() List~Task~
        +find_conflicts() List~Tuple~Task, Task~~
        +conflict_warnings() List~str~
        +schedule_tasks() List~Task~
        +build_plan(strategy str) Plan
        +occurrences_between(start date, end date) List~Tuple~Pet, Task~~
        +mark_task_complete(task Task) None
        +create_next_occurrence(task Task) Task?
    }

    class PlanEntry {
        +Pet pet
        +Task task
        +datetime requested_start
        +bool moved
        +bool flexible
    }

    class Plan {
        +List~PlanEntry~ scheduled
        +List~Tuple~Pet, Task, str~~ unscheduled
        +explain() List~str~
    }

    Owner "1" o-- "0..*" Pet : owns
    Owner "1" o-- "0..*" Window : availability
    Pet "1" o-- "0..*" Task : has
    Task ..> Recurrence : parses frequency
    Scheduler "1" --> "1" Owner : plans for
    Scheduler ..> Task : sorts / filters / detects conflicts
    Scheduler ..> Window : finds free slots
    Scheduler ..> Plan : produces
    Plan "1" *-- "0..*" PlanEntry : contains
    PlanEntry --> Task : places
    PlanEntry --> Pet : for

    note for Window "A scheduling interval represented in code as tuple[datetime, datetime]. Owner stores available and unavailable windows; Scheduler subtracts placed tasks and unavailable windows to find free slots."
    note for Task "due_date + start_time are the single source of truth; start_datetime composes them. Fixed tasks run at start_time; flexible tasks (earliest_start..latest_end) let the scheduler pick. buffer_minutes reserves a quiet gap after the task. recurrence parses frequency; calculate_next_start()/with_datetime() build the next occurrence."
    note for Recurrence "Parsed repeat rule: once, daily/weekly/monthly/yearly, every N days/weeks/hours, or weekday sets. occurrences_in() jumps straight to the first occurrence in range (O(1)) instead of stepping period by period."
    note for Scheduler "Central coordinator used by the app: sort_by_time() and filter_tasks() feed the task table; conflict_warnings()/find_conflicts() feed alerts; build_plan() reflows conflicts into free slots instead of dropping them. strategy='greedy' places by priority, strategy='optimal' uses weighted interval scheduling (DP) to keep the max-priority set. occurrences_between() previews recurring tasks without mutating pets."
    note for Plan "The explained result: scheduled PlanEntries (moved / flexible flags) plus unscheduled (pet, task, reason). explain() renders human-readable lines."
